  <assign id="4">
    <name>Assignment #2: Do a Number of the Day with your students and reflect</name>
    <intro>&lt;h3&gt;Do a Number of the Day with your students and reflect&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 1.231;"&gt;Introduce Number of the Day to your students. This activity can help adult learners understand the structure of numbers, see patterns, diversify their use of operations, and expand their knowledge of symbols and notation. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For two weeks, open each class by doing a Number of the Day. In small groups, learners will work together to come up with as many answers as they can. As a large group, discuss the students’ answers, exploring how they came up with them, and determining what is clear and what is confusing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Write a two- to three-paragraph reflection on what you learned in doing this exercise with your students. (Click Add or Edit my submission)&lt;/p&gt;</intro>
